# Satellite (src/p2_satellite) PRODUCTION runtime dependencies only.
#
# Compiled to requirements.txt via pip-tools (MIT):
#   pip-compile --generate-hashes --output-file=requirements.txt requirements.in
#
# core-side-patch/ dependencies deliberately do NOT belong in this file --
# the satellite must never import anything from core-side-patch/ or vice
# versa (agent-push / inbound-only rule, see PATENT.md). Its dependencies
# (sqlalchemy, pgvector, alembic, pyvis, ...) live in requirements-dev.in
# instead, since they're only needed to run THIS demo repo's test suite
# (which happens to colocate both sides -- see
# core-side-patch/ASSUMPTIONS.md item 13), not to run the satellite itself.
# See core-side-patch/requirements-additions.txt for what the REAL core repo
# would need for core-side-patch/ once merged there.

